The Pakistan Automotive Manufacturers Association is a trade group of automobile manufacturers that operate in the Pakistan. It is the leading advocacy group for the Pakistan auto industry. Licensed by the Ministry of Commerce under the Trade Organizations Ordinance 2007, PAMA is committed to developing constructive solutions to public policy challenges that promote sustainable mobility and benefit society in the areas of environment, energy and motor vehicle safety. PAMA also serves as the central source of statistical data for the automotive industry.
